    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  NVX-CoV2373 is an adjuvanted recombinant full-length SARS-CoV-2 spike trimer protein vaccine demonstrated to be protective against COVID-19 in efficacy trials. Here we demonstrate that vaccinated subjects made CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cell responses after one and two doses of NVX-CoV2373, and a subset of individuals made CD8\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cell responses. Characterization of the vaccine-elicited CD8\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cells demonstrated IFN\n                  <jats:italic>\u03b3</jats:italic>\n                  production. Characterization of the vaccine-elicited CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cells revealed both circulating T follicular helper cells (cT\n                  <jats:sub>FH</jats:sub>\n                  ) and T\n                  <jats:sub>H</jats:sub>\n                  1 cells (IFN\n                  <jats:italic>\u03b3</jats:italic>\n                  , TNF\u03b1, and IL-2) were detectable within 7 days of the primary immunization. Spike-specific CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cells were correlated with the magnitude of the later SARS-CoV-2 neutralizing antibody titers, indicating that robust generation of CD4\n                  <jats:sup>+</jats:sup>\n                  T cells, capable of supporting humoral immune responses, may be a key characteristic of NVX-CoV2373 which utilizes Matrix-M\u2122 adjuvant.\n                </jats:p>",
